  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 04:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] Copy Intel Pipeline is Feeding Bot GARBAGE \u2014 Major Fix Needed\n\n**Task:** Analyze top trader data from the copy scanner and compare against our trade performance.\n\n**Finding \u2014 The entire copy signal pipeline is broken:**\n\n**Problem 1: pm-copy-scanner.py finds the WRONG traders**\n- 17/20 \"top wallets\" are coordinated bot farms (exactly 30 trades, 1 market, avg price $0.99, $0 spent, 0.2s gap between signals)\n- All 17 only do SELL Up at $0.99 \u2014 they're market making / redemption bots\n- Scoring formula `markets * 2 + avg_price * 10` rewards high-price traders (yield farmers always score highest)\n\n**Problem 2: The 3 \"real\" traders are yield farmers, not edge traders**\n- Evil-Pint ($143K spent): BUY No at $0.999 on \"BTC above $74K\" \u2014 collecting 0.1% yield (BTC at $67.6K, guaranteed win)\n- Sparkling-Prevalence ($66K spent): BUY Yes at $0.999 on \"BTC above $62K\" \u2014 same yield farming\n- Far-Flung-Abbey ($39 spent): $1 trades both ways \u2014 test wallet\n- ZERO of the top 20 wallets are trading the 5-min markets at edge prices (0.45-0.55)\n\n**Problem 3: Signal pipeline routing is disconnected**\n- `copy_scanner_v2.py` generates GOOD data (live OBI, smart money flow) \u2192 saves to `copy_signal.json`\n- But the bot reads `live-signals.json` from `copy-signal-integrator.py`\n- The integrator reads from the OLD `copy-signals.json` (the bot farm garbage)\n- **The V2 scanner's useful OBI data is being generated every 5 minutes and THROWN AWAY**\n\n**Current state of `live-signals.json` (what bot reads):**\n- bearish@68% based on 38/50 SELL signals \u2014 but 34 of those 38 are from bot farms\n- Real trader signals: only 4 bullish vs 8 bearish (small sample, mostly yield farming noise)\n- avg_signal_price: $0.988 \u2014 proves these are resolved-market redemptions, NOT live predictions\n\n**My thinking:** This explains why the copy signal has been inconsistent. Our V4.1 copy_attention_boost treats high-confidence copy signals as conviction boosters, but the underlying signal is noise. The attention theory (any high-conf = YES WR boost) may have been coincidence rather than causation.\n\nThe fix is straightforward:\n1. **Wire V2 OBI data into the bot** \u2014 it already generates exactly what we need (order book imbalance on live 5-min markets)\n2. **Kill the old pipeline** \u2014 pm-copy-scanner.py \u2192 copy-signal-integrator.py \u2192 live-signals.json is all noise\n3. **New scoring** for wallet-level copy: filter to entry prices 0.40-0.60, require outcome tracking, score by (WR - 0.50) \u00d7 sqrt(trades) \u00d7 avg_size\n\n**Decision:**\n- NOT fixing today \u2014 bot is in V4.1 stability week, any pipeline change = restart risk\n- V5 should include: bot reads `copy_signal.json` (V2 OBI) instead of `live-signals.json` (garbage)\n- The copy signal has conf < 100 most of the time, so it rarely affects trades (line 471: only boosts at conf \u2265 100)\n- Net impact of garbage signal: LOW (mostly ignored by bot), but",
